					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Pentateuch, Hafṭarot and Five Scrolls, provided with punctuation, accents and masorah parva.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n79066420">
							<locus from="1r" to="265v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torah, megilot ṿe-hafṭarot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תורה, מגילות  והפטרות </title>
							<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
							<note>
								<p>The fullest masorah is given to the Pentateuch; in the Hafṭarot  and the Five Scrolls only the קרי is given. </p>
								<p>See <ref target="Sed-Rajna_1970" type="page">74-75</ref>, <ref target="Sed-Rajna_1988" type="page">16-17</ref>, <ref target="BL_2007" type="page">40</ref>, <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">66-67</ref>. </p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="other">5 frontispieces in colours and gold.<locus n="1r, 48v, 88r, 114v, 152r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">
								<locus n="242v, 248v, 255r, 258v"/>4 decorated initial-word panels in colours and gold.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="other">1 embellished panel in colours and gold.<locus n="245v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="other">1 embellished panel with pen-flourishing, in mauve ink. <locus n="42r"/>
							</decoNote>
						</msItem>
